reviewText: The title says Complete but it is not unless they never finished making it. Disk 5 leaves you at the start of what feels like a big battle then fade to black, credits. Would love to know if there is more to this. Not knowing how it ends is kinda annoying. The story is decent and I personally enjoyed it until the last episode where it just stops.

Has a great plot and a few interesting characters.  I watched this a long time ago in the 90's, but I never saw the last episode, I was very disappointed to find that the final episode cliffhangers, there's no finishing of the storyat all.
This anime was very good, loved it would love to know if there is going to be a continuation of this anime?
This didn't work in my DVD player.  It only worked in my computer, and just wasn't up to par.  Wouldn't buy again.

This is done by the same person that has done La Blue Girl and Urotsukidoji (AKA, The Overfiend series) and I was really disappointed. I thought the Overfiend series was one of the best Hentai series on the market. La Blue girl was okay but still not as good. This series started out okay, and laid ground for a decent story but failed to follow through. The thought of the demons bringing hell on earth was a good opener in the first of five parts, but as it goes on the plot gets weaker. By the last disc I was just thinking, wow, that's it? I don't regret buying it, I don't feel I wasted my time on it, I just think this series had a potential to be so much better. If you are going into this thinking that it will be like Overfiend, think again. If you just like freaky demon sex, then go ahead and grab it!
